patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Nicholas Kingston was born about 1240, in Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Nicholas Kingston."},"et":{"Abt 1240–":"umbes 1240–Surnud","1246–Female":"1246–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","Abt 1240":"umbes 1240","about 1270":"umbes 1270","1246":"1246","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England","of Tortworth,Gloucestershire,England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1240–":"noin 1240–Kuollut","1246–Female":"1246–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","Abt 1240":"noin 1240","about 1270":"noin 1270","1246":"1246","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England","of Tortworth,Gloucestershire,England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1240–":"environ 1240–Décédé","1246–Female":"1246–Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","1270–Female":"1270–Décédée","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","Abt 1240":"environ 1240","about 1270":"environ 1270","1246":"1246","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","Tortworth, Gloucestershire, England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Angleterre","of Tortworth,Gloucestershire,England":"Tortworth, Gloucestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Nicholas Kingston est né environ 1240, à Tortworth